<doc id="872613" wikidata="Q7389465" url="?curid=872613" title="SDMA">
<text>SDMA may refer to:

* Symmetric dimethylarginine, an exogenous isomer of asymmetric dimethylarginine (ADMA) that is used as a renal function tracer/biomarker to diagnose chronic kidney disease
* Space-division multiple access, a channel access method used in communication (for instance in MIMO technology)
* Soft direct memory access, a type of direct memory access (DMA) specific to Xilinx&#x27;s Multi-Port Memory Controller (MPMC)
* System direct memory access, a Linux kernel module and userspace library for accessing direct memory access (DMA) using some processors made by Texas Instruments</text><links>
