<doc id="872843" wikidata="Q16734906" url="?curid=872843" title="Rakaa">
<text>Rakaa Taylor (born June 18, 1972) better known by his stage names Rakaa, Rakaa Iriscience, and Iriscience, is a rapper from Los Angeles, California. He is a member of Dilated Peoples alongside Evidence and DJ Babu.

==Life and career==
His mother was a half Korean adoptee who was born in Korea during the Korean War and came to the United States at an early age.

Rakaa released the solo debut album, &quot;Crown of Thorns&quot;, on Decon in 2010. It featured vocal contributions from Aloe Blacc, KRS-One, Chali 2na, Evidence, and Fashawn. It was produced by Exile, DJ Babu, Oh No, El-P, and The Alchemist.

